posts.subject: >tfw you defeat a paywall by simply blocking a script

posts.body: Oh boy, here we go again. Except this time there's no reply limit.

>>58e399bf-fa33-4140-a822-515727033056
Kinda, but it's not '''that''' bad. Because the seed ratio stays the same, it's just that there are less peers on any given file. And peers who download can generate the lower quality files themselves in the background if they have spare CPU power, so even that problem is mitigated.

posts.subject: Why the fuck does Loonix need to "generate locales"?
posts.body: Is this another case of the famous Unix brain damage? Why not just deliver the locales among the other files provided by the installer?
